    "summary": "Dr. Paschalis Pechlivanis is Assistant Professor in History of International Relations at the Department of History and Art History, Utrecht University. His research interests lie at the intersection of International History and International Relations, with a specific focus on the Cold War, US Foreign Policy and post-1945 European and Balkan History. His monograph 'America and Romania in the Cold War: A Differentiated D\u00e9tente, 1969-80' (A Romanian edition of the book is forthcoming by Editura Litera) examines the US foreign policy of differentiation towards the socialist regimes of Eastern Europe as it was implemented by various administrations towards Ceausescu\u2019s Romania from 1969 to 1980. Dr. Pechlivanis is currently developing his next project \"A Cold War Microcosm: The Balkans from 1945 to 1989\".\n\nHe studied Law (LLB) at Aristotle University of Thessaloniki (2009), International Relations (MScEcon, Distinction) at Aberystwyth University (2012) and he obtained his PhD in History from the European University Institute (EUI), Florence in 2017. During his PhD he has been a visiting researcher at New York University and he has previously taught at the University of Florence, Italy.",
